translated: Östberg, Einar Wilhelm Otto, hospital physician, Växjö, b. 14/5/99 in Lands-kr. to bank cashier Otto Emil Ö. and Hilda Elisabeth Grönwall. M. 31 with Monica Löwegren. Children: Görel Monica Anna Elisabeth b. 32, Per-Otto Ivar b. 34, Björn Otto Michaél b. 38, Clas Otto b. 43. — Studied: graduated from high school in Malmö in 17, medical candidate in 21, medical licentiate in 26 and medical doctor in 31, all at Lund University. Assistant clerk at the anatomy institute in Lund 20-21, clerk there in 24, medical intern and assistant physician in the radiology department there 25-27, assistant intern and physician at the medical clinic in Lund 28-32, acting clinical laboratory technician at Lund University 32-33, teacher in clinical diagnostics in 32 and leader of the course in general medical technology the same year, various teaching appointments at the medical clinic in Lund 30-32, lecturer in practical medicine at Lund University 34-38, clinical laboratory technician and assistant teacher in medicine 36-38, chief physician at RamBsa 36-38, hospital physician at Växjö hospital medical department since 39. Publications: dissertations and papers in physiological chemistry and internal medicine.
